---
title: CSS Pie Chart
description: A pie chart drawn with `conic-gradient()` — no SVG, no JavaScript.
slug: pie-chart
cssFile: pie-chart.css
explanation: "`conic-gradient()` creates a gradient that sweeps around a center point — perfect for pie charts. Each color stop defines a slice: `conic-gradient(red 0% 35%, blue 35% 60%)` creates a red slice covering 0°–35% and a blue slice from 35%–60%. Combining with `border-radius: 50%` turns the square into a circle. A donut variant adds a second radial-gradient mask in the center using `background` shorthand with multiple layers."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="chart-wrap">
	<div>
		<div class="pie pie-simple"></div>
		<p class="chart-title">Pie chart</p>
	</div>
	<div class="legend">
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--coral)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Category A</span>
			<span class="legend-val">35%</span>
		</div>
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--sky)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Category B</span>
			<span class="legend-val">25%</span>
		</div>
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--accent)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Category C</span>
			<span class="legend-val">20%</span>
		</div>
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--violet)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Category D</span>
			<span class="legend-val">20%</span>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="chart-wrap" style="margin-top:1rem">
	<div>
		<div class="pie pie-donut"></div>
		<p class="chart-title">Donut variant</p>
	</div>
	<div class="legend">
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--accent)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Revenue</span>
			<span class="legend-val">42%</span>
		</div>
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--sky)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Cost</span>
			<span class="legend-val">23%</span>
		</div>
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--coral)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Tax</span>
			<span class="legend-val">20%</span>
		</div>
		<div class="legend-item">
			<span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--yellow)"></span>
			<span class="legend-label">Other</span>
			<span class="legend-val">15%</span>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="pie"></div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
/* Pie chart */
.pie {
  width: 160px;
  height: 160px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: conic-gradient(
    var(--coral)   0% 35%,
    var(--sky)     35% 60%,
    var(--accent)  60% 80%,
    var(--violet)  80% 100%
  );
}

/* Donut variant — mask the center */
.pie-donut {
  background:
    radial-gradient(circle at center, var(--bg) 50%, transparent 50%),
    conic-gradient(
      var(--accent)  0% 42%,
      var(--sky)     42% 65%,
      var(--coral)   65% 85%,
      var(--yellow)  85% 100%
    );
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
